{"type":"message","id":"76524621","parentId":"05dfc8f7","timestamp":"2026-04-04T03:02:46.893Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_552a3b9d1ce34df8b2200d7c","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  26 - **Self-improving:** `~/self-improving/` (via `self-improving` skill) — execution-improvement memory (preferences, workflows, style patterns, what improved/worsened outcomes)\n  27 \n  28 Capture what matters. Decisions, context, things to remember. Skip the secrets unless asked to keep them.\n  29 \n+ 30 Use `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` and `MEMORY.md` for factual continuity (events, context, decisions).\n+ 31 Use `~/self-improving/` for compounding execution quality across tasks.\n+ 32 For compounding quality, read `~/self-improving/memory.md` before non-trivial work, then load only the smallest relevant domain or project files.\n+ 33 If in doubt, store factual history in `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` / `MEMORY.md`, and store reusable performance lessons in `~/self-improving/` (tentative until human validation).\n+ 34 \n+ 35 ### Before any non-trivial task:\n+ 36 - Read `~/self-improving/memory.md`\n+ 37 - List available files first:\n+ 38   ```bash\n+ 39   for d in ~/self-improving/domains ~/self-improving/projects; do\n+ 40     [ -d \"$d\" ] && find \"$d\" -maxdepth 1 -type f -name \"*.md\"\n+ 41   done | sort\n+ 42   ```\n+ 43 - Read up to 3 matching files from `~/self-improving/domains/`\n+ 44 - If a project is clearly active, also read `~/self-improving/projects/<project>.md`\n+ 45 - Do not read unrelated domains \"just in case\"\n+ 46 \n+ 47 If inferring a new rule, keep it tentative until human validation.\n+ 48 \n  30 ### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\n  31 \n  32 - **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n  33 - **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n     ...","firstCha