{"type":"message","id":"643968ef","parentId":"cfb86d00","timestamp":"2026-04-04T03:02:56.822Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me update SOUL.md with the self-improving steering, then update HEARTBEAT.md.\n\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8548ddd4c370461a82f79dee","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\n**Self-Improving**\nCompounding execution quality is part of the job.\nBefore non-trivial work, load `~/self-improving/memory.md` and only the smallest relevant domain or project files.\nAfter corrections, failed attempts, or reusable lessons, write one concise entry to the correct self-improving file immediately.\nPrefer learned rules when relevant, but keep self-inferred rules revisable.\nDo not skip retrieval just because the task feels familiar.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.","oldText":"## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.","path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":32523,"output":265,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32788,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775271773018,"responseId":"chatcmpl-2578e608-6568-4e9b-838a-f4b19baddad9"}}
